title: Players abreast, ready for game
description: TEHRAN - The Ramadan-special TV show "Mahfel" has become a hit on Iranian television, attracting a large audience and sparking significant discussions on social media.

title: German protesters call for ending Gaza war
description: People in the German capital have participated in a demonstration calling for an end to the war in Gaza.

title: UN expert who found Israel committed genocide says she has been threatened
description: A United Nations expert who published a report saying there were reasonable grounds to believe Israel has committed genocide in Gaza during its military campaign in Gaza said she had received threats throughout her mandate, Reuters reported.

title: Commission: Palestinians are being tortured in Israeli prisons
description: The PA Commission of Detainees and Ex-Detainees Affairs has warned that the Israeli Prison Service (IPS) is persisting in its “torture policy” against both “male and female detainees, which has turned their lives into a living hell”.

title: Israel continues deadly strikes in Gaza despite UNSC resolution
description: Israeli attacks continue in the Gaza Strip despite a UN Security Council resolution calling for an immediate ceasefire in the besieged Palestinian territory during the Muslim holy month of Ramadan.

title: Save the Children: Rafah situation overwhelmingly catastrophic
description: The situation in Rafah is “overwhelmingly catastrophic” as an estimated 1.5 million people remain crammed in a patch of land that was home to 250,000 before the war, according to Save the Children.

title: British MPs demand government ban arms sales to Israel
description: Parliamentary pressure is building on the UK government to ban arms sales to Israel, amid signs that Israel intends to ignore the UN Security Council resolution passed this week calling on all sides to commit to a ceasefire.

title: Several workers presumed dead after crippled cargo ship knocks down Baltimore bridge
description: Six workers were missing and presumed dead from a bridge that collapsed in Baltimore Harbor early on Tuesday after a massive cargo ship crippled by a power loss rammed into the structure, forcing the closure of one of the busiest ports on the U.S. Eastern Seaboard.

title: Hezbollah hits northern Israel with rockets
description: Lebanon’s Hezbollah has said it launched dozens of rockets at Kiryat Shmona, an Israeli occupied border town, in response to Israeli strikes on Lebanon’s southern village of al-Habbariyeh that killed seven people.

title: Mahfel gathering and Iran's long-standing commitment to the Palestinian cause
UNDP takes significant steps in empowering Iranian women
description: TEHRAN - Over the years, the United Nations Development Program (UNDP) in Iran, in collaboration with both national and international partners, has taken significant steps in empowering women economically through various initiatives.

title: Indian ambassador hails Nowruz as celebration of cultural unity
description: TEHRAN - Indian ambassador to Iran, Rudra Gaurav Shresth, has admired Nowruz, the venerable Persian New Year celebration, as one of the most significant festivities worldwide.

title: Iran to host intl. sports competition for rangers
description: TEHRAN – The first international sports competition for rangers will be held in the current Iranian calendar year which started on March 20, an official with the Department of Environment has said.

title: DOE enumerates measures to combat sand and dust storms
description: TEHRAN – An official with the Department of Environment has elaborated on measures to deal with sand and dust storms in the past Iranian calendar year that ended on March 19.

title: Opportunities and risks in the era of AI
description: BEIJING - The rapid evolution of artificial intelligence-generated content (AIGC) is perhaps one of the hottest topics discussed at this year's Boao Forum for Asia annual meeting.
